@startuml 01-reverse-proxy
title Nginx as a Reverse Proxy (High-Level)

skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam defaultFontName Consolas

actor "Client A" as A
actor "Client B" as B
actor "Client C" as C
actor "...10k+ clients" as N

node "NGINX\nport 80 / 443" as NGINX #LightBlue

node "Backend 1\napp:3000" as B1
node "Backend 2\napp:3001" as B2
node "Backend 3\napp:3002" as B3

A --> NGINX
B --> NGINX
C --> NGINX
N --> NGINX

NGINX --> B1 : proxy_pass
NGINX --> B2 : proxy_pass
NGINX --> B3 : proxy_pass

note right of NGINX
  Sits between many clients
  and a few backend workers.
  Handles TLS, load balancing,
  caching, and rate limiting.
end note

@enduml
